dcterms:description: The Wordle dataset consists of data from the Wordle game, where players have six attempts to guess a five-letter word, receiving feedback on the correctness of their guesses. This dataset is used to evaluate the performance of offline reinforcement learning methods.
dcterms:title: Wordle Dataset

dcterms:description: The Visual Dialogue dataset is designed for training agents to engage in dialogue about images, where the agent must ask and answer questions based on visual content. The dataset is used to evaluate the ability of models to optimize various reward functions in dialogue settings.
dcterms:title: Visual Dialogue Dataset

dcterms:description: The Reddit Comments dataset consists of 4 million comments scraped from Reddit, used to train models for generating replies based on context. The dataset is characterized by its diversity and the presence of subjective and noisy reward functions.
dcterms:title: Reddit Comments Dataset
